{"info": {"author": "Andrea Dittadi", "author_email": "andrea.dittadi@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python"], "description": "# easy-notify\n\nSmall cross-platform Python package for basic OS notifications.\n\n\n## Compatibility\n\n- OS: macOS, Ubuntu, Windows 10\n- Python 2 and 3\n\n\n## Installation\n\n```\npip install easy-notify\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```\nfrom easy_notify import notify\nnotify(\"Title\", \"Message\")\n```\n\nIf the optional argument `sound` is omitted, the notification will have the default system sound. If it is `None`, no sound will be played. If it's a string, the specified sound will be played if available in the system. See `example.py` for examples in Linux and macOS.\n\n\n## Notes\n\nFor the moment, when used on Windows 10, the package relies on `win10toast`, which doesn't seem to support sound customization.\n\nIcons are not supported for now, but it should be easy on all platforms.\n\nIt should also work on older (but not too old) versions of Mac, and it could work on distros other than Ubuntu.\n\nSee https://github.com/KDE/snoretoast for more features in Windows 10 maybe.\n\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/addtt/py-notifications", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "easy-notify", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easy-notify/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easy-notify/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/addtt/py-notifications"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/easy-notify/0.0.2/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": ">=2.7", "summary": "Simple cross-platform desktop notifications with Python", "version": "0.0.2", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>easy-notify</h1>\n<p>Small cross-platform Python package for basic OS notifications.</p>\n<h2>Compatibility</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>OS: macOS, Ubuntu, Windows 10</li>\n<li>Python 2 and 3</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre><code>pip install easy-notify\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><code>from easy_notify import notify\nnotify(\"Title\", \"Message\")\n</code></pre>\n<p>If the optional argument <code>sound</code> is omitted, the notification will have the default system sound. If it is <code>None</code>, no sound will be played. If it's a string, the specified sound will be played if available in the system. See <code>example.py</code> for examples in Linux and macOS.</p>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<p>For the moment, when used on Windows 10, the package relies on <code>win10toast</code>, which doesn't seem to support sound customization.</p>\n<p>Icons are not supported for now, but it should be easy on all platforms.</p>\n<p>It should also work on older (but not too old) versions of Mac, and it could work on distros other than Ubuntu.</p>\n<p>See <a href=\"https://github.com/KDE/snoretoast\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/KDE/snoretoast</a> for more features in Windows 10 maybe.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6977492, "releases": {"0.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2795c8b84364a01e25935cf29aa670f9", "sha256": "531c3380fedcdcb7461ff0ae817b5154354f73416131883834e222762b4b34b3"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "easy_notify-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2795c8b84364a01e25935cf29aa670f9", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=2.7", "size": 3660, "upload_time": "2020-04-08T12:35:07", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-08T12:35:07.323510Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/0b/72/98757f92c3c29d635e6d3932f56e8334b846fc8dfd21d8df5bb18931d271/easy_notify-0.0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digest